<div id="review_1387566779" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1387566779" />
    <a title="Ashley Warner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17509206-ashley-warner"><img alt="Ashley Warner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442946328p2/17509206.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1387566779?book_show_action=true">Sep 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashley Warner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashley Warner" href="/user/show/17509206-ashley-warner">Ashley Warner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1387566779" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2154815491077810480"><i>Beautiful Affliction</i> offers a compelling account of Fogelberg’s daily physical challenges with debilitating heart disease and the haunting isolation suffered as her deadly symptoms are repeatedly dismissed. At last, a dramatic series of events will have even the most doubtful believing in miracles, and we will all be reminded of the sustaining power of love.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


