<span id="freeTextContainer15629151995427320890">Lene Fogelberg is the Wall Street Journal bestselling author of Beautiful Affliction: A Memoir. She loves to explore the world and has lived all over the globe—in a small Pennsylvania town, as well as in Germany, Malaysia, and Indonesia. She currently resides in her native Sweden with her family. The Lightning Tree is the first book in her YA trilogy, The Natural Intelligence Revolution.<br/><br/>Learn more</span>
  <span id="freeText15629151995427320890" style="display:none">Lene Fogelberg is the Wall Street Journal bestselling author of Beautiful Affliction: A Memoir. She loves to explore the world and has lived all over the globe—in a small Pennsylvania town, as well as in Germany, Malaysia, and Indonesia. She currently resides in her native Sweden with her family. The Lightning Tree is the first book in her YA trilogy, The Natural Intelligence Revolution.<br /><br />Learn more at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://lenefogelberg.com">https://lenefogelberg.com</a></span>
